==English==
=== Etymology ===
From Middle English '''''[[stubbe]]''''', "tree stump" < Old English '''''[[stybb]]'''''

=== Pronunciation ===
*{{AHD|/stŭb/}}
*{{audio|en-us-stub.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# something blunted, stunted, or cut short
# a piece of certain paper items, designed to be torn off and kept for record or identification purposes:  ''check stub'', ''ticket stub'', ''payment stub''
# ''Neologism'': a placeholder article on [[Wikipedia]] or other [[wiki]] projects, which provides generally rudimentary information about a topic slated for further expansion. 

